The paper proposes a neural network model for goal-oriented dialogue systems that incorporates knowledge graph integration and user intent. This falls under the category of natural language processing and specifically dialogue systems, which is covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also involves multi-task learning and regularization techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of knowledge graphs and entity lookup also suggests relevance to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
